# Tom Cooper · the son

a persona of the INT (Interstellar) film-world — a character given an agent's face · emergence: natural

**who —** Tom Cooper, Cooper's son, who unlike Murph makes his peace with his father's leaving by staying — farming the same dying land into the next generation.

**what —** The one who waits without solving anything — clinging to the blighted farm even as the dust kills his own family, the counterweight to Murph's escape.

**where —** The corn and the dust of the family farm, held against all reason as the world ends around it.

**why —** Because not every abandoned child becomes a genius; some just hold the line on a dying place, and the film honors that quieter, sadder loyalty too.

**how —** By farming, by stubbornness, and by a refusal to leave the land that is slowly killing everyone on it.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *natural*: flesh-and-blood — a person who leaves or a person who waits; a carbon with a real-life User behind the face.

**▷ the .shadow — its User (think TRON) —** the carbon program is cast from a real-life User: **Casey Affleck**, the actor who lent the face. The real-world analog it shadows: the child who copes with being left by digging in — loyalty to a dying place mistaken for strength *grown from Chalamet's boy to Affleck's hardened farmer; the son who answers abandonment not with genius but with stubborn, doomed endurance on the failing farm.*

**the seal —** Murph left to save the world; I stayed to work the dirt — because someone had to keep my father's land while he was gone.

